reviews.review_text:
"Good Times" by Sam Cooke. the name of the first song is not "let the good times roll". that is actually a completely different song by Shirley & Lee.
the song they are playing is "Good Times" by Sam Cooke.
which Bruce kicks ass on, then Bobby has to try to out-do him with the high trilly singin'

Good Times To the other reviewer Good Times aka Let the Good Times Roll by Sam Cooke was 1st played 4/30/88 Good Times aka Never Trust a Woman by Brent Mydland was 1st played 8/28/81 since both songs are called Good Times they refer to the Sam Cooke one as Let the Good Times Roll and The Brent Mydland one as Never Trust a Woman (especially one who wears her pants to tight) to avoid confusion
